description:
Statue of Liberty Nebula in Narrowband HOO&SHO
HOO: Original revision and B 
SHO:  Revision C
H-alpha: 6×300s  O-III: 9×300s  S-II: 3×300s
Me and one of my friend together rent Chilescope 1m RC to image this spectacular region. We were so excited when we got the frames and I was shocked when I finished the process-so many details and such amazing shape with so many dark filaments around it! This region looks like Statue of Liberty flying in the sky, or a warrior is about to kill the crocodile around his belt. Hope you like the image:)
imaging_cameras: FLI Proline 16803 CCD camera CCD digital camera
imaging_telescopes: ASA - ASTRO SYSTEME AUSTRIA ASA RC 1000
title: Statue of Liberty in the sky HOO&SHO
